annotation.TEXT: Whoa, lucky stomp! More coins here? Nope, a 1-up this time. That's not really a surprise.
There was that crazy flame again, but somehow, I didn't hit it this time. If only I could reliably dodge it like that when I'm not invincible.
Alright, now this time, I'll just let the platform go on its merry way, waiting an additional ten game seconds before aiming for 6 fireworks.
Whoops. Well, I got the 6, but somehow only got 2000 from the flagpole... and now I think I'm stuck.
Space-time rewind count: 12
Fake Kaizo trap count: 7
Well, I think I have time for one more level.
Yep, just verifying that there was indeed a fifth OMNOMNOM-er there.
Well, I guess I had to restart the level, so... Let's enter the first bonus room here, as it's easier and worth 26 more coins than using the invisible coin blocks to cross the gap.
Alright, I'm back here. Now, let's not drop down to any of the lower platforms over here this time.
Woo! A star!
Why am I wasting time getting coins here?
Really, game? Sigh... Let me work my way back...
Umm... Yep. That moving platform somehow glitched Mario, and now his tongue is stuck to this flagpole. I can still pause/unpause, but that's about it. Guess I'll have to time-travel again...
Heck, yeah! ...Oh, geez. I'm actually running out of time here! Alright, screw the rest of the pipes!
Alright, I just barely avoided getting a fish in the face as I got the star there. Since this castle has so many stars, maybe this won't be so bad.
Nuts. I thought I could make that jump. There might've been hidden coin blocks around there for me to use.
Well, that's no good. And I was holding A, B, and right there. So, that midpoint's broken, and I'll have to go back in time again. Seriously, were these midpoints never tested?
Gotta check every pipe...
I debated whether to go over the top there, but then just decided to exit here and now.
There's no way I'm entering that underwater room again, though! (Unless the game forces me to somehow.)
Huh, where am I now?
Yeah, game. That was totally fair.
Whoa, my star! Whoa, my platform! Well, at least there's another platform down here, but I missed the star and a bunch of coins (and who knows what else).
Dang it! For a split-second, I thought I'd be dealing with a bullet generator instead, but nope. Flying cheepos.
How did nothing massacre me as I went for those ? blocks?
And, since I'm big now, I'll try to clip through the wall to get three more 1-ups here.
How is nothing massacring me now?
Okay, I can still see that first platform up ahead. I wonder if I can catch up to it...
Once again, avoid the water area, because it sucks. And, let's do that big leap here again, since it worked so well last time!
Hey there, Toad. How's it going? BANZAIII!!!
Aha, found more hidden coin blocks!
Demo count: 26
Oh, no! Not this place again! Honestly, were the flying cheepos really necessary in this so-called "bonus" room?
Oh, right. That just leads to this 28-coin room. Well, if I ever need to restart the level again, there's no reason not to enter this coin room at least once at the beginning of the level.
Star chain: 4
Star chain: 3
Okay, good. I've reached the goal.

Well, now that I'm in world 6, Bowser's throwing hammers, not that I care with my star power. However, I'm burninating him here since that's worth more points than star-killing him. (And I may as well star-kill the Podoboo a few times while I'm here.)
OMNOMNOM! Delicious!
Space-time rewind count: 11
Ah, this pipe goes places. And I can get 28 coins while I'm here.
Demo count: 25
Eat it, Buzzy!
And I've found another pipe that takes me to the same place. Well, this is good, because I can become fiery now. Also, I'll exit here instead of going to the right for the 1-ups again.
Oops. Was coming down here a mistake?
Wait, what am I doing? Wow, that big leap actually worked?! Awesome!
Okay, let's see what's further to the right over here. (If the video looks glitched right here, I blame YouTube, as my original video isn't glitched here.)
Demo count: 24
Yep, although I fell from the sky instead of coming out of the pipe.
8-life combo! Alright, that's all I'm doing with that.
Alright, now how will 6-4 be different from 1-4? There'd better not be flying cheepos...
Yeah, just keep swimming, fishy. (If you stomp a fish that's swimming like that in a non-water level, it turns into a koopa, strangely enough.)
Also, that flagpole is close enough to the stairs that it can easily be leapt over without the platform, but I checked later, and there's nothing but endlessness (until time expires) beyond.
Ooh, can I get this to work this time?
Fortunately, that Buzzy wasn't a problem.
No, I'm not going to check those lower pipes, since I'm kind of in a hurry here.
I clipped through that wall surprisingly quickly!
Those Hammer Duders are stuck in the ceiling, so nuts to them.
Now, this time, let's reveal the coin blocks without somehow falling into the gaping jaws of an OMNOMNOM-er!
And now I have crown-W lives, which is 42 lives. Next time, I'll be starting with world 7-2 (and hope I don't begin with an unavoidable cheepo up my butt)! To be continued...
Hello, and welcome back to New Strange Mario Bros.! Let's see how lost I get in the pipes of world 6-2...
Star chain: 2
Yeah, I figured there'd be hidden coin blocks here.
Well, this pipe kind of cut the star short, but as long as I don't have to deal with flying cheepos when I emerge, I'm fine with that.
Did I seriously just do that? LOL.
I almost forgot that I want to enter the 28-coin room here.
Death count: Infinity+3
Somehow, I suspect that this short pipe here is the exit from the underwater area. Whoa, that's a lot of pipes. I bet at least one will take me somewhere.
Aha! Ooh, this pipe's good! I needed a chance to power up!
Ha! That Buzzy is no match for me!
Alright, I guess I can forget about that first platform, since I encountered another one at the same height.
Whoa! Okay, let's not try acting like this is a danmaku game and just get out of here!
Oh, god. More flying cheepos? And tons of bullet cannons as well, though I think the first three are non-functional.
Huh. I can go right back down and get another 28 (or 27... oops) coins.
Whoop. That platform's a dropper. Also, looks like I'm approaching the goal. My moving platform should make it easy to hit the top of the flagpole, but can I time it correctly for 6 fireworks?
Oh, I do believe this level looks familiar. It's a non-underwater version of world 0-2 (or rather, world 0-2 is an underwater version of this level).
I think I'll grab three 1-ups while I'm here. Oh, wait. Since I moved all the way over here, doesn't that mean that I'll emerge in an earlier part of the level?
